    {"q": "What is Ohm's law?", "a": "Ohm's law states that the current through a conductor between two points is directly proportional to the voltage across the two points."},
    {"q": "What is a transformer?", "a": "A transformer is an electrical device that changes the voltage of alternating current (AC) in a circuit."},
    {"q": "What is electromagnetic induction?", "a": "Electromagnetic induction is the process by which a changing magnetic field induces an electric current in a conductor."},
    {"q": "What is the difference between series and parallel circuits?", "a": "In a series circuit, components are connected end-to-end, while in a parallel circuit, components are connected across common points."},
    {"q": "What is the function of a fuse?", "a": "A fuse is a safety device that protects electrical circuits by melting and breaking the circuit if the current exceeds a certain level."},
