  {"q": "What is condensation?", "a": "Condensation is the process where a gas changes into a liquid when it loses heat."},
  {"q": "What is freezing?", "a": "Freezing is the process where a liquid turns into a solid by losing heat."},
  {"q": "What is sublimation?", "a": "Sublimation is the direct change from solid to gas without passing through the liquid state."},
  {"q": "What is deposition?", "a": "Deposition is the change of a gas directly into a solid without becoming a liquid."},
  {"q": "How does temperature affect particle movement?", "a": "As temperature increases, particles gain kinetic energy and move faster."},
  {"q": "Why do gases expand more than solids and liquids?", "a": "Gases expand more because their particles are far apart and move freely, filling any container."},
